quran[6]{c,v,t,f}:
  6,133,"And your Lord is the Free of need, the possessor of mercy. If He wills, He can do away with you and give succession after you to whomever He wills, just as He produced you from the descendants of another people."
  6,134,"Indeed, what you are promised is coming, and you will not cause failure [to Allāh].{1}",footnotes:1:[i.e., You will neither escape nor prevent its occurrence.]
  6,135,"Say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., in the land or in the Hereafter.]
  7,43,"And We will have removed whatever is within their breasts of resentment,{1} [while] flowing beneath them are rivers. And they will say, ",footnotes:1:[i.e., ill will or sense of injury for what was inflicted upon them during worldly life.]
  7,44,"And the companions of Paradise will call out to the companions of the Fire, "
  7,45,"Who averted [people] from the way of Allāh and sought to make it [seem] deviant while they were, concerning the Hereafter, disbelievers."